:: DESCRIPTION or/and USES ::
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Locking the System
 Before you lock the system, please note that the unlock hotkey is h by default, you press the button h on your keyboard to unlock the locked system. You can change the unlock hotkey in the configuration at any time.

 

You can lock the system by:

 Clicking the Lock Now button on the main window of the Desktop Lock.

You just launch the Desktop Lock, then click the Lock Now button, the system will then be locked.

 Using the lock hotkey.

You can lock the system directly with the global lock hotkey, by default there is not a lock hotkey after you installed the software, you can specify one in the Lock Settings. It's a system global hotkey, you don't need to launch the main program of Desktop Lock to use the hotkey.

Note the Lock Hotkey is NOT the unlock hotkey, it can not be used to unlock the system. For more information, see Unlock hotkey.

 Letting it lock the system automatically.

Desktop Lock can be configured to lock the system after computer booted. It also supports to lock the system when the system becomes idle. You can also setup the schedule options to let Desktop Lock to lock and/or unlock the system automatically at any time you specified.

For more information, see Advanced Settings and Schedule Settings.

Unlocking the Locked System
When you want to unlock the locked system, you just simply press the default unlock hotkey h. You press this key on your keyboard, the system then will be unlocked. 

Desktop Lock supports to unlock the system with the unlock hotkey, mouse actions etc., it also can be applied an unlock password which will be asked before the Desktop Lock can actually unlock the system. For more information, see Unlock Settings.

 

The unlock hotkey is not a normal Windows hotkey, you don't hold all the keys in the hotkey, instead you will press each key in the hotkey continuously. Please read the information about the unlock hotkey in the Unlock Settings section.
